Q: Huh?

A: This is both an individualized continuation of the &quot;Recommended Reading Round-up&quot;
   project and my debut contribution to &lt;a href=&quot; http://thepiratebay.se/user/STFmaryville&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt; http://thepiratebay.se/user/STFmaryville&lt;/a&gt;  's
   &quot;Not Reading&quot; initiative. Which merging of concepts I actually managed to cram 
   into the title, after a fashion, at the price of an (even for me) unusually high 
   degree of grammatical-convolution-per-character density. :P


Q: So, what's on the menu this month?

A: The first Dark Horse volume of Victor Santos' &quot;Polar&quot;, aka &quot;Black Kaiser&quot;.

   You'll probably like this if you already like any of the following:

    - Ian Fleming's &quot;James Bond&quot; books and/or the resultant movies;
    - Frank Miller's &quot;Sin City&quot; books;
    - the Hard-Boiled/Noir genre, generally speaking;
    - the &quot;Show, Don't Tell&quot; principle, even more generally speaking.

   You'll *definitely* like this if you liked the premise of Warren Ellis' &quot;RED&quot;
   (and/or the resultant movies, I suppose, considering that the premise is pretty
   much all they have in common), but found his execution a bit lacking and trite.

   Sample: &lt;a href=&quot; http://image.bayimg.com/12ba9217ab285036651ec5eb3c68e71f5a746e2c.jpg&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt; http://image.bayimg.com/12ba9217ab285036651ec5eb3c68e71f5a746e2c.jpg&lt;/a&gt;

   (My favourite page, both for the elegant paneling and because it's the lead-in 
   to a strikingly story-boarded sequence of scrumptiously squicky slaughter.)
